SIMPLE: speciality
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Speciality
<hw>Spe`ci*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Specialities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[See <er>Special</er>,
and <er>Specialty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A particular or peculiar
case; a particularity.</def> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>See <er>Specialty</er>,
3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The special or peculiar mark or characteristic of a
person or thing; that for which a person is specially distinguished; an
object of special attention; a special occupation or object of
attention; a specialty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On these two general heads all other <qex>specialities</qex> are
depedent.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Strive, while improving your one talent, to enrich your whole
capital as a man. It is in this way that you escape from the wretched
narrow-mindedness which is the characteristic of every one who
cultivates his <qex>speciality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ld.
Lytton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We 'll say, instead, the inconsequent creature man, -⟦br⟧
For that'a his <qex>speciality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Think of this, sir, . . . remote from the impulses of passion, and
apart from the <qex>specialities</qex> -- if I may use that strong
remark -- of prejudice.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An attribute or quality peculiar to a
species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Specialization</ent>⟦br⟧
